Step 1: Set Up Azure OpenAI (Core Services)

Here’s how we’ll get your Azure OpenAI environment fully functional:

⸻

A. Create an Azure OpenAI Resource
	1.	Go to the Azure Portal: https://portal.azure.com
	2.	Click Create a resource
	3.	Search for: Azure OpenAI
	4.	Click Create
	5.	Fill in the details:
	•	Subscription: (your active one)
	•	Resource group: Create new (e.g., SIAConnectRG)
	•	Region: MUST be a supported region (as of now: East US, South Central US, West Europe, France Central)
	•	Name: SIAConnectAI
	•	Pricing Tier: Standard (Pay-As-You-Go)
	6.	Click Review + Create, then Create

⸻

B. Retrieve Your Azure OpenAI Keys + Endpoint

Once your resource is deployed:
	1.	Go to SIAConnectAI (or whatever you named it)
	2.	Click Keys and Endpoint
	3.	Copy:
	•	Your Key
	•	Your Endpoint URL
You’ll use both in Power Automate and Copilot flows.

⸻

C. Deploy a Model (GPT-4 Turbo or GPT-3.5)
	1.	In your Azure OpenAI Resource:
	2.	Go to Model Deployments
	3.	Click + Create
	4.	Choose:
	•	Model: gpt-4 (or gpt-35-turbo)
	•	Deployment name: SIA_GPT4Turbo
	•	Version: Latest available
	5.	Click Deploy

This creates a live deployment endpoint you can use in Power Automate via HTTP.

⸻

D. Verify You Have These Permissions

You’ll need:
	•	Cognitive Services Contributor role on the resource
	•	Access to Power Automate in the same tenant (we’ll use the HTTP action)
	•	Optional: Assign yourself or your app to the Azure OpenAI User role if using REST API elsewhere

⸻

Step 2: Prep Power Automate for Azure OpenAI Calls

We’ll use an HTTP action to call the GPT-4 Turbo model directly.

Required:
	•	Resource deployment name (e.g., SIA_GPT4Turbo)
	•	Your Key
	•	Endpoint URL (https://<your-region>.openai.azure.com/openai/deployments/<deployment-name>/chat/completions?api-version=2024-02-15-preview)
